user_prompt_template:
CHAPTER NARRATIVE (read this carefully — every rule, trigger, scenario, and metric must come directly from this content):
{chapter_narrative}

CHAPTER PLAN:
{current_chapter_json}

PROJECT CONTEXT:
Life Event: {life_event}
Document: {document_title}
Audience: {audience}
Tone: {tone}
Context: {context}

Generate the structural elements for {domain_name}. Every element must be directly grounded in the narrative provided above and feel custom-written for {life_event}.

QUICK REFERENCE RULES (5–8 rules):
  • Surface the most critical operational decisions from the narrative
  • Each rule must be immediately actionable by a non-expert in this specific situation
  • Format: "[Specific actionable rule] — Rationale: [the specific failure mechanism this rule prevents]. Trigger: [the specific condition that activates this rule — not 'when needed']. Risk: [the concrete, named consequence of ignoring it — include a dollar amount, time penalty, or irreversible outcome]."

SCENARIO SCENE (required — 3–5 sentences):
  A real-world mini-story showing this chapter's system working as designed.
  Requirements: named person + specific time of day or deadline + at least one real number + outcome that would NOT have happened without the system.
  Written in present tense. The story must be specific enough that it could not appear unchanged in a manual for a different life event.

SUCCESS METRICS (3–5 metrics):
  Specific, quantified outcomes the operator achieves when this chapter's system works.
  Each metric must include at least one real number: hours saved, dollars protected, days avoided, hospitalizations prevented, legal deadlines met, or risks neutralised.
  No vague improvements. No 'better outcomes' or 'improved coordination'.

CASCADE TRIGGERS:
  Name the conditions in this chapter that activate required actions in other domains.
  Format: "When [specific event or output in this chapter], immediately trigger [specific named action] in [named domain]."

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "chapter_number": {chapter_number},
  "domain_id": "domain ID from the chapter plan",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter title from the plan",
  "quick_reference_rules": [
    "[Specific actionable rule] — Rationale: [specific failure mechanism prevented]. Trigger: [specific condition]. Risk: [concrete named consequence with number or legal outcome]."
  ],
  "cascade_triggers": [
    "When [specific event or output in this chapter], immediately trigger [specific named action] in [named domain]"
  ],
  "scenario_scene": "3–5 sentence present-tense mini-story. Named person, specific time or deadline, at least one real number, outcome that required the system. Must be specific to {life_event}.",
  "success_metrics": [
    "Specific quantified outcome — must include at least one real number (hours, dollars, days, count, or risk)"
  ]
}}
